    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Price of Stopping Terrorists</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Robert A Dudley letter on irony of super-sophisticated missiles of US destroyer Cole being rendered useless by two men in a little boat (Oct 14 military analysis)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Superpower Suddenly Finds Itself Threatened by Sophisticated Terrorists'' (military analysis, Oct. 14):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Superpower Suddenly Finds Itself Threatened by Sophisticated Terrorists'' (military analysis, Oct. 14):</p>
        <p>The super-sophisticated missiles of the United States destroyer Cole are an instructive metaphor for the proposed national missile defense system.</p>
        <p>To attack the ship, the rogues were much too clever to seek comparably sophisticated weapons of their own; it was easier to use two men in a little boat.</p>
        <p>ROBERT A. DUDLEY  Boulder, Colo., Oct. 14, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
